  "target_response": {
    "text": "That sounds more like delayed-onset muscle soreness than an injury, based on the context you gave. The leading contributor is the new stimulus: a first heavy squat session commonly lines up with quad soreness in the 24 to 48 hour window. The second clue is pattern: both quads, dull muscle ache, and easing as you warm up would fit DOMS; sharp, one-sided, joint-centered pain or swelling would change the read. Your recovery score is 68% with HRV at 61 ms, close to your 62 ms baseline, so there is not a systemic warning in the data either. For today, use easy walking, light cycling, or gentle mobility only, and skip hard quad loading until the ache is clearly settling.",
